<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Jenny K Walsh — Links</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Funnel+Display:wght@300..800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      background: #fff;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      font-family: 'Funnel Display', sans-serif;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 60px 20px 80px;
      max-width: 560px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .greeting {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .block {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .block p {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #1a1a1a;
    }

    .link-btn {
      display: inline-block;
      align-self: flex-start;
      font-family: 'Funnel Display', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      background: #F6FF00;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem;
      transition: box-shadow 0.1s steps(2), transform 0.1s steps(2);
    }

    .link-btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 6px 3px 0 #00FFFF, -6px -3px 0 #FF00FF;
    }

    .link-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }

    .divider {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .bye {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1 class="greeting">Oh, hi there!</h1>

  <div class="block">
    <p>You're looking for some sort of link — let's see if I can help you.</p>
    <p>I exist in far too many places across the web, an inevitable artifact of being online since the mid-90s. Can't do much about it, so here are a few places you'll find me.</p>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <div class="block">
    <p>This is my product design portfolio.</p>
    <a class="link-btn" href="https://jennykwalsh.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Product design portfolio</a>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <p>There's always YouTube, where I have some acro and circus videos as well as yurt stuff and #1SecondEveryday videos.</p>
    <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <p>If you'd like to see more of my photography, I have a client gallery at Form &amp; Pixel Photography that captures a small portion of it.</p>
    <a class="link-btn" href="https://formpixelphotography.pic-time.com/client" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Form &amp; Pixel Photography</a>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <p>I've also got instas for Roland and Pixel, which they rarely update but still get more engagement than I do (deservedly so).</p>
    <div class="link-row">
      <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Roland on Instagram</a>
      <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pixel on Instagram</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <p>For pottery, I've got both a shop and an instagram.</p>
    <div class="link-row">
      <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pottery shop</a>
      <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pottery on Instagram</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="block">
    <p>Other socials, if you're into that kinda thing.</p>
    <div class="link-row">
      <a class="link-btn" href="https://www.threads.net/@lemonjenny" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Threads</a>
      <a class="link-btn" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pinterest</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <div class="block">
    <p>There's more, dating back to Geocities and OG Blogger and all manner of old websites I've built... but we're gonna let those die in the archives.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="bye">Bye!</p>

</body>
</html>
